# Training Plan — EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE

Copy this file to your Tempo data dir as `plan.md` (default `~/.tempo/plan.md`)
and edit it freely. Tempo reads it for *context only* (PLAN-02) — it does not
diff planned-vs-actual (a deliberate non-goal). The whole file is available to
analyses; in addition, a few light `Key: value` lines near the top are surfaced
verbatim in the race-readiness report so your current focus is front and centre.

Recognised light fields (optional, first occurrence wins): `Phase`, `Week`,
`Focus`, `Mileage`, `Target`, `Block`.

Phase: Base building
Week: 6 of 16
Focus: aerobic volume + one tempo per week; long run building toward 30 km
Mileage: ~70 km/week, ramping ~10% / 3 weeks then a down week
Target: Berlin Marathon sub-3:15

## Notes

- Easy runs strictly easy — keep most volume conversational.
- One quality session midweek (tempo or threshold), one long run at the weekend.
- Deload every 4th week (drop volume ~30%).

## This week

- Mon: rest
- Tue: 12 km easy
- Wed: 5 km w/u, 6 km @ threshold, 3 km c/d
- Thu: 10 km easy
- Fri: rest
- Sat: 14 km easy + strides
- Sun: 28 km long run
